Three persons were confirmed dead Thursday in an accident that occurred at the Ekwu hills along the BÃ©nin-Auchi highway. Seven others were said to have been critically injured. Witnesses said the accident involved a Toyota Camry car marked CF 404 AKD, a truck laden with fuel marked MUA 308 XA, an 18-seater commercial bus and a black Totoya Prado Jeep marked AKD 902 AS. Edo Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Mr. Anthony Oko, who confirmed the incident, said both the dead and injured were taken to Irrua Specialists Hospital. Oko attributed the accident to over speeding. He said a team of FRSC officials were drafted to the scene of the crash to remove the debris and help to control traffic.